TOPIC: 'Survivor'in Texas?; No problem -- and we're not talking road-kill.
GRAPHIC: Central Texas boasts three types of edible mulberries., Cactus pads, or nopalitas, are edible, and prickly pears make a purple margarita. // We had a little too much fun with our state mammal, courtesy of Congress Avenue Card and Gift Shop, but we do have a point. Armadillo is edible, as are the mulberries, dandelion greens and prickly pears. In fact, half of the species of plants in a typical Central Texas pasture offer something to eat.  Among wildflowers in Texas, primroses are edible -- but bluebonnets and Indian paint brush are not. Vegetarians can get by just fine on the fat of the Central Texas land. This veggie platter includes native mulberries, primrose, dandelion greens, dandelion flowers and, of course, pecans.  Survivor cuisine,Texas-style If you know your state flower from your state mammal, you can survive out back in the Lone Star state
